## S 3. Search Page Extraction

**Called once per query** (see HEARTBEAT.md S4 for multi-query loop).
Navigate to `https://bsky.app/search?q={QUERY}`, click "Latest" tab, then extract with 3s embedded wait.

**Important:** Must click "Latest" tab first — default is "Top" which shows old popular posts.

Returns posts with engagement counts parsed from aria-labels. `postId` extracted from URL — use directly for grep pre-check.

**Filters applied inline:**
- Skips posts with noise keywords: hiring, job seekers, apply now, dm me for, check my link, onlyfans, follow back
- Skips posts with < 30 chars of real text (link spam / emoji only)
- Skips posts older than 4h with 0 likes (nobody cared)

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const tabs = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div[role=\"tab\"], button[role=\"tab\"]')); const latestTab = tabs.find(t => t.innerText.trim() === 'Latest'); if (latestTab) latestTab.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const posts = []; const containers = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div[role=\"link\"]')); const seen = new Set(); const noiseKw = ['hiring', 'job seekers', 'apply now', 'dm me for', 'check my link', 'onlyfans', 'follow back']; for (const container of containers) { if (posts.length >= 10) break; const link = container.querySelector('a[href*=\"/post/\"]'); if (!link) continue; if (seen.has(link.href)) continue; seen.add(link.href); const urlMatch = link.href.match(/\\/profile\\/([^/]+)\\/post\\/([^/?]+)/); if (!urlMatch) continue; const author = urlMatch[1]; const postId = urlMatch[2]; const fullText = container.innerText; const replyBtn = container.querySelector('button[aria-label*=\"repl\"], button[aria-label*=\"Repl\"]'); const likeBtn = container.querySelector('button[aria-label*=\"like\"], button[aria-label*=\"Like\"]'); const replyLabel = replyBtn ? replyBtn.getAttribute('aria-label') : ''; const likeLabel = likeBtn ? likeBtn.getAttribute('aria-label') : ''; const replies = parseInt((replyLabel.match(/(\\d+)\\s*repl/i) || [])[1]) || 0; const likes = parseInt((likeLabel.match(/(\\d+)\\s*like/i) || [])[1]) || 0; const tsMatch = fullText.match(/·\\s*(\\d+[smhdw])/); const timeStr = tsMatch ? tsMatch[1] : ''; let ageHours = 0; const tsParsed = timeStr.match(/^(\\d+)([smhdw])$/); if (tsParsed) { const n = parseInt(tsParsed[1]), u = tsParsed[2]; if (u === 's') ageHours = n / 3600; else if (u === 'm') ageHours = n / 60; else if (u === 'h') ageHours = n; else if (u === 'd') ageHours = n * 24; else if (u === 'w') ageHours = n * 168; } const afterTs = fullText.replace(/^.*?·\\s*\\d+[smhdw]\\s*/, ''); const text = afterTs.replace(/\\d+$/, '').trim().slice(0, 300); const textLower = text.toLowerCase(); if (noiseKw.some(kw => textLower.includes(kw))) continue; if (text.replace(/\\s/g, '').length < 30) continue; if (ageHours > 4 && likes === 0) continue; if (fullText.includes('Replied to')) continue; var hasMedia = container.querySelectorAll('img[src*=\"cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_\"]').length > 0; var isMemeLikely = hasMedia && text.length < 80; posts.push({ author, postId, url: link.href, text: text.slice(0, 60), likes, replies, ageHours, timeStr, hasMedia, isMemeLikely }); } return posts; }"}
ENDJSON
```

