## S 4a. Duplicate Check + Post Text (combined, on post page)

After navigating to post. Combines 3s wait + DOM duplicate check + post text read into ONE evaluate.

**Duplicate check:** Look for our profile link inside thread **reply** containers (role="link"), skipping the first one (the OP post itself). When we're the OP, our profile appears in the first container — that's not a duplicate comment.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const mainContent = document.querySelector('main') || document.body; const threadContainers = Array.from(mainContent.querySelectorAll('div[role=\"link\"]')); const replyContainers = threadContainers.slice(1); const inReplyLinks = replyContainers.flatMap(c => Array.from(c.querySelectorAll('a[href*=\"/profile/{{handle}}\"]'))); const alreadyCommented = inReplyLinks.length > 0; var composeBtn = document.querySelector('button[aria-label=\"Compose reply\"]'); var composeY = composeBtn ? composeBtn.getBoundingClientRect().y : 9999; var parentChainLen = threadContainers.filter(c => c.getBoundingClientRect().y < composeY).length; var tooDeep = parentChainLen >= 4; const postText = mainContent.innerText.slice(0, 500); return { alreadyCommented, tooDeep, parentChainLen, text: postText }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `alreadyCommented: true` → backfill to `memory/commented_posts.txt`, skip to next candidate.
If `tooDeep: true` (parentChainLen >= 4) → skip (deep thread, no visibility).

## S 4b. Click Reply Button (for post pages)

Use when commenting on posts. Clicks "Compose reply" which opens the reply dialog.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const composeBtn = document.querySelector('button[aria-label=\"Compose reply\"]'); if (!composeBtn) return { error: 'no_compose_button' }; composeBtn.click(); return { clicked: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

After clicking, the 1.5s wait is embedded in S 5 (Reply/Comment Flow).

