## S 6. Click Quote

**Step 1:** Click repost button:
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const repostBtn = document.querySelector('button[aria-label=\"Repost or quote post\"]'); if (!repostBtn) return { clicked: false, error: 'no_repost_btn' }; repostBtn.click(); return { clicked: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 2:** Click "Quote post" menu item (with 1s embedded wait):
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); const menuItems = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div[role=\"menuitem\"]')); const quoteItem = menuItems.find(m => m.innerText.trim() === 'Quote post'); if (quoteItem) { quoteItem.click(); return { clicked: true }; } return { clicked: false }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 3:** Use BROWSER-core.md S 5 but with `button[aria-label="Publish post"]` as submit button (NOT "Publish reply").

